@node "Desc" "Wozu?"
===============================================================================
Auf die Schnelle:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
@{"Magic Adreþmanager III" Link "Copy" } (short MAMIII) can be used for easy managing of
Addresses, creating "Serienbriefe" (what's the english word for it? serial-
letters?) for remembering of Birthdays and for dialing numbers via modem.

Features:

- Supports additional Text- and Grafik-Files
- uses MUI
- very easy to use
- reminds you of birthdays
- dials telephon numbers
- uses locale.library (supports german and english)
- ARexx-Port
- Converter for ADM and DFA-DBs
- 8 Databases in one
- Shortcuts for quick group-selection
- skip own dialling code
...

===============================================================================

@endnode

@node "Reqs" "Requirements"

===============================================================================

AMIII requires:
              * AmigaOS Version 2.04+
              * @{"MUI - MagicUserInterface" Link "MUI"} V2.2+
              * A Screenmode whith min. 256 lines

Recommended:
              * Harddisk (never wrong :) )
              * AmigaOS Version 3.0+ (Datatypes, faster screens)
              * @{"rexxreqtools.library" Link "Copy"} (ARexx-Scripts)
              * A Screenmode with min. 400 lines
              * Processor > 68000 (faster listscrolling) 

Recommended tools:
"PowerSnap" from Nico FranÁois (fd).
"Clip Board Enhancer" from Anthony J. Moringello (Shareware).

===============================================================================

@EndNode


@node "Use" "Usage"

===============================================================================

MAMIII has 3 different modes. The @{"Workbench-Mode" Link "WB"} (doubleclick on the MAM-Icon
or with the option "-GUI") offers you the MUI-GUI. The @{"Shell-Mode" Link "SHELL"}
(getting started by calling the programm form a shell without the "-GUI" 
option) returns depending on the option information about birthdays or tel.-
numbers. For the @{"ARexx-Mode" Link "AREXX"} you have to start MAM in the workbenchmode 
first, then you can remote control MAM via ARexx (e.g. from a textprocessor).

===============================================================================

@endnode

@node "WB" "Workbench-Mode"
 
===============================================================================

 @{"    New entry      " Link "NEW"}    Creates a new entry
 @{"   Copy entry      " Link "COPYGD"}    Copies an entry                    
 @{"      Dial         " Link "DIAL"}    Dials the telefonnumber via Modem
 @{"   Show entry      " Link "SHOW"}    Displays the entry                
 @{"   Change entries  " Link "CHANGE"}    chages the marked entries
 @{"   Delete entries  " Link "DEL"}    Deletes the marked entries
 @{"   Filter entries  " Link "FILTER"}    Filters certain entries

 @{"  Change groups    " Link "CLASS"}    Changes the groupnames       
 @{"    Fast dial      " Link "FASTDIAL"}    Changes the fastdialing entries
 @{"     Settings      " Link "PREFS"}    Chaanges the programsettings

 @{"       QUIT        " Link "QUIT"}    Quits the program

see also: @{"Pulldown-Menues" Link "Menu"}
          @{"Keys" link "KEY"}

multiselect: hold down the shift-key and select the entries with the mouse.

===============================================================================

@endnode


